  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 830 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vietnamese-chicken-bowls-5d2ca6625839a1000a511a3b
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Asian
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim and halve @Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into thin halfmoons.

Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped) leaves and stems. Zest and halve @lime{1}(zested and halved). Thinly slice @chili pepper{1}(thinly sliced), removing seeds for less heat.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, half the lime zest, half the cilantro, and juice from one lime half. Season with plenty of @salt{plenty} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{20-30%seconds}. Reduce heat to low and stir in @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, half the @sriracha{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1%tablespoon}, and juice from remaining lime. Simmer, stirring, until thickened and syrupy, ~{30 seconds to 1%minute}. Turn off heat.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and remaining sriracha. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in remaining lime zest and @butter{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide between bowls.

Thinly slice chicken. Top rice with chicken and salad. Drizzle chicken with sauce. Garnish with sriracha mayo, remaining cilantro, and chili to taste.